The paper describes a computational methodology for learning algebraic functions from data, which is a common problem in machine learning. The approach involves building a low-complexity linear model and refining it using error maximization sampling and derivative-free optimization. This methodology is applicable to a wide range of problems, including reaction problems, and can enforce constraints on the response variables. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the use of optimization techniques suggests the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as possible categories.
